    "description": "If you're a passionate Senior Financial Analyst with drive and ambition, Grant Thornton India South Asia Partners in Gwalior is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Grant Thornton India South Asia Partners:\nGrant Thornton India South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Ensure compliance with tax regulations and statutory requirements\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• CA / CMA / CFA certification\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Python for Finance\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Flexible working hours\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gwalior, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Grant Thornton India South Asia Partners!",
